    dc:creator "Medianero, Enrique; Nieves-Aldrey, José Luis" ;
    dc:date "2010" ;
    dc:title "The genus Amphibolips Reinhard (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini) in the Neotropics, with description of three new species from Panama" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275715>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275716>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275719>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275720> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275715>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Amphibolips aliciae: (A) Head anterior view. (B) Pronotum anterior view. (C) Mesosoma lateral view. (D) Mesosoma dorsal view. (E) Metasoma lateral view. (F) Propodeum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/275715/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275716>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Amphibolips aliciae: (A) Female antenna. (B) Detail of basal flagellomeres. (C) Detail of last flagellomeres. (D) Metatarsal claw. (E) Male antenna. (F) Detail of last flagellomere of male antenna. (G) Detail of basal flagellomeres of male antenna." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/275716/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275719>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Habitus and forewings of Amphibolips species: (A) Amphibolips castroviejoi, female (B) A. castroviejoi, male (C) forewing of female. (D) Amphibolips aliciae. (E) forewing of female. (F) A. salicifoliae, female. (G) A. salicifoliae, male. (H) forewing of female." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/275719/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275720>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Galls of Amphibolips species from Panama: (A) Immature gall of Amphibolips castroviejoi. (B) Group of mature galls. (C) Section of a gall showing the central cell with the larvae of a gregarious parasitoid. (D) Mature gall of Amphibolips aliciae. (E) Section of a dry gall. (F) An old A. aliciae gall showing the exit holes of parasitoid species. (G) Amphibolips salicifoliae leaf gall. (H) Section of a mature gall." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/275720/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

